translated: Cederberg, Johan Allan, provincial doctor, born in Rödeby on October 8, 1898, died in Tofte-ryd, Jönköping County, son of Albert C. and Jenny Johansson. Married in 1933 to Ingrid Margareta Forsell with whom he had three children: Bengt Allan (born 1934), Inger Elisabeth (born 1935), and Axel Lennart (born 1942). He passed his studentexamen in Växjö in 1919, completed a Bachelor of Medicine degree in Lund in 1925, and a medical license in Stockholm in 1930. He worked as an assistant doctor and physician in Eksjö lasaret, Vimmerby, Nässjö, and Hofors districts from 1930 to 1932, as acting second lieutenant at Kronprinsessan Victorias kustsanatorium in the same year, and as second lieutenant there from 1933 to 1934. He served as first lieutenant at Hålahults sanatorium from 1934 to 1935, then as a physician at Hudiksvalls lasarett from 1935 to 1936, acting second lieutenant there from 1936 to 1938, acting provincial doctor in Ljungskile district in 1938, a physician at Ulmeken's sjukhem in 1939, provincial doctor in Grönskåna district from 1943 to 1947, and in Rödeby district from 1947 until his death.
